<subSubSection id="C30C650CE926593DFF14FDF6FF15FAB8" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA93687E926593DFF14FDF6FAB8FCF8" blockId="6.[151,1437,542,1397]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFF14FDF6FEB1FD90" bold="true" box="[199,322,578,605]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A large subgenus without apparent synapomorphy. Characterized by generally broader wings than other 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFF0AFDDCFEDBFD4C" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1807" box="[217,296,616,641]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Emesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFF0AFDDCFEDBFD4C" box="[217,296,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Emesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="132D2A02E926593DFEE9FDD3FE7CFD4F" box="[314,399,615,642]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1235,1260]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,185,1210]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[164,1423,181,1210]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sequenced specimens of new genera and subgenera proposed in this study. Dorsal and ventral sides are shown on the left and right, respectively, with the image letter in between. Gray letter F indicates that the mirror image (left-right invert- ed) is shown. DNA sample numbers are indicated for specimens, see Table S1 for other data. a. Curvie emesia, NVG-18045F09, on the right are male genitalia (with a 0.5 mm scale bar) of the specimen NVG-11913, data as for NVG-11914 (Table S1), but eclosed on 15-Feb-1974; b. Emesis (Mandania) mandana, NVG-18044D09; c. Emesis (Poeasia) poeas, NVG-18044G04; d. Emesis (Brimia) brimo, NVG-18045E01; e. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG-18054D08; f. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG- 18054D09; g. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG-18054D10; h. Emesis (Tenedia) tenedia, NVG-18086H06; i. Befrostia elegia syntype male, NVG-18052H02; j. Befrostia elegia syntype male, Brazil, coll. H. Stichel, 1089, NVG-18052H04; k. Befrostia elegia syntype female, no data, NVG-18052H03; l. Befrostia lalannei holotype, NVG-18086H06.All syntypes shown are from the ZMHB collection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449866/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Fig. 2h</figureCitation>
). It is best diagnosed by the lack of characters for other subgenera. Differs from the nominotypical subgenus by the lack of metallic spots, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFD2CFD3FFC9AFD68" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[767,873,651,677]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Aphacitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFD2CFD3FFC9AFD68" box="[767,873,651,677]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Aphacitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the lack of apical white spots in females, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFF44FD04FF02FD04" box="[151,241,688,713]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Emesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Poeasia">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFF44FD04FF02FD04" box="[151,241,688,713]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Poeasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="132D2A02E926593DFED1FD1BFEA0FD04" box="[258,339,687,713]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1235,1260]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,185,1210]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[164,1423,181,1210]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sequenced specimens of new genera and subgenera proposed in this study. Dorsal and ventral sides are shown on the left and right, respectively, with the image letter in between. Gray letter F indicates that the mirror image (left-right invert- ed) is shown. DNA sample numbers are indicated for specimens, see Table S1 for other data. a. Curvie emesia, NVG-18045F09, on the right are male genitalia (with a 0.5 mm scale bar) of the specimen NVG-11913, data as for NVG-11914 (Table S1), but eclosed on 15-Feb-1974; b. Emesis (Mandania) mandana, NVG-18044D09; c. Emesis (Poeasia) poeas, NVG-18044G04; d. Emesis (Brimia) brimo, NVG-18045E01; e. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG-18054D08; f. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG- 18054D09; g. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG-18054D10; h. Emesis (Tenedia) tenedia, NVG-18086H06; i. Befrostia elegia syntype male, NVG-18052H02; j. Befrostia elegia syntype male, Brazil, coll. H. Stichel, 1089, NVG-18052H04; k. Befrostia elegia syntype female, no data, NVG-18052H03; l. Befrostia lalannei holotype, NVG-18086H06.All syntypes shown are from the ZMHB collection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449866/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
) by the lack of broad gray semi-metallic areas on wings, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFBF3FD1BFB60FD04" box="[1056,1171,687,713]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Emesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mandania">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFBF3FD1BFB60FD04" box="[1056,1171,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Mandania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="132D2A02E926593DFB70FD1BFB05FD07" box="[1187,1270,687,714]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1235,1260]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,185,1210]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[164,1423,181,1210]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sequenced specimens of new genera and subgenera proposed in this study. Dorsal and ventral sides are shown on the left and right, respectively, with the image letter in between. Gray letter F indicates that the mirror image (left-right invert- ed) is shown. DNA sample numbers are indicated for specimens, see Table S1 for other data. a. Curvie emesia, NVG-18045F09, on the right are male genitalia (with a 0.5 mm scale bar) of the specimen NVG-11913, data as for NVG-11914 (Table S1), but eclosed on 15-Feb-1974; b. Emesis (Mandania) mandana, NVG-18044D09; c. Emesis (Poeasia) poeas, NVG-18044G04; d. Emesis (Brimia) brimo, NVG-18045E01; e. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG-18054D08; f. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG- 18054D09; g. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG-18054D10; h. Emesis (Tenedia) tenedia, NVG-18086H06; i. Befrostia elegia syntype male, NVG-18052H02; j. Befrostia elegia syntype male, Brazil, coll. H. Stichel, 1089, NVG-18052H04; k. Befrostia elegia syntype female, no data, NVG-18052H03; l. Befrostia lalannei holotype, NVG-18086H06.All syntypes shown are from the ZMHB collection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449866/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
) by less bulky body, and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFE9BFD60FE65FD20" box="[328,406,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Emesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Brimia">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFE9BFD60FE65FD20" box="[328,406,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Brimia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="132D2A02E926593DFE76FD67FE05FD23" box="[421,502,723,750]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1235,1260]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,185,1210]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[164,1423,181,1210]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sequenced specimens of new genera and subgenera proposed in this study. Dorsal and ventral sides are shown on the left and right, respectively, with the image letter in between. Gray letter F indicates that the mirror image (left-right invert- ed) is shown. DNA sample numbers are indicated for specimens, see Table S1 for other data. a. Curvie emesia, NVG-18045F09, on the right are male genitalia (with a 0.5 mm scale bar) of the specimen NVG-11913, data as for NVG-11914 (Table S1), but eclosed on 15-Feb-1974; b. Emesis (Mandania) mandana, NVG-18044D09; c. Emesis (Poeasia) poeas, NVG-18044G04; d. Emesis (Brimia) brimo, NVG-18045E01; e. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG-18054D08; f. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG- 18054D09; g. Xanthosa xanthosa syntype, NVG-18054D10; h. Emesis (Tenedia) tenedia, NVG-18086H06; i. Befrostia elegia syntype male, NVG-18052H02; j. Befrostia elegia syntype male, Brazil, coll. H. Stichel, 1089, NVG-18052H04; k. Befrostia elegia syntype female, no data, NVG-18052H03; l. Befrostia lalannei holotype, NVG-18086H06.All syntypes shown are from the ZMHB collection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449866/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
) by relatively larger hindwings. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: nuclear genome: cne11306.1.2:T60A, cne5833.2.1:A108G, cne12476.6.1:A395G, cne18163.3.1: A186G, cne 
<date id="FFA81047E926593DFEF3FCAEFE75FCF8" box="[288,390,794,821]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" value="2337-05-01">2337.5.1</date>
:A603T; COI barcode region: T281R, T484M, G506A or G38A &amp; T283A, and A520T.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA93687E926593DFF14FC8AFEC0FCB3" blockId="6.[151,1437,542,1397]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFF14FC8AFE17FC94" bold="true" box="[199,484,830,857]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Derivation of the name.</emphasis>
