Fabricius, 1807
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA93687E926593DFF14FBD4FF15FAB8" blockId="6.[151,1437,542,1397]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">
Next, our genomic analysis revealed that some species placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFC72FBD4FC03FBB4" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1807" box="[929,1008,1120,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Emesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFC72FBD4FC03FBB4" box="[929,1008,1120,1145]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Emesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not belong in that genus. In agreement with morphological analysis of Hall &amp; Harvey (2002), genomic phylogeny places 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFBA9FB30FF2AFB0C" authority="(Stichel, 1919)" authorityName="Stichel" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1919" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Emesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthosa">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFBA9FB30FAC5FB50" box="[1146,1334,1155,1181]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Emesis xanthosa</emphasis>
(Stichel, 1919)
</taxonomicName>
as a sister of 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFEA2FB1CFD25FB0C" authority="(Stichel, 1910)" authorityName="Stichel" authorityYear="1910" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[369,726,1191,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFEA2FB1CFDD5FB0C" box="[369,550,1192,1218]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Sertania guttata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B76E926593DFDE6FB13FD3CFB0C" author="Stichel, H." box="[565,719,1191,1217]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" pagination="1 - 452" refId="ref10228" refString="Stichel, H. (1910 - 1911) Fam. Riodinidae. Allgemeines. Subfam. Riodininae. Vol. 112. In: Wytsman, J. (Ed.), Genera Insectorum. Desmet-Verteneuil, Brussels, pp. 1 - 452." type="book chapter" year="1910">Stichel, 1910</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="54AD8825E926593DFCD8FB1CFCC8FB0F" box="[779,827,1192,1218]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">type</typeStatus>
species of a genus described recently (
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B76E926593DFB3CFB13FF27FB28" author="Kaminski, L. A. &amp; Callaghan, C. J. &amp; Seraphim, N. &amp; Magaldi, L. M. &amp; Volkmann, L. &amp; Freitas, A. V. L." pageId="6" pageNumber="481" pagination="165 - 179" refId="ref9793" refString="Kaminski, L. A., Callaghan, C. J., Seraphim, N., Magaldi, L. M., Volkmann, L. &amp; Freitas, A. V. L. (2017) Sertania gen. nov., a new genus of butterflies (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae) from the South American dry diagonal. Zootaxa, 4312 (1), 165 - 179. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4312.1.8" type="journal article" year="2017">
Kaminski 
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFAB7FB1CFA66FB0C" box="[1380,1429,1191,1217]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). The difference between COI barcodes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFD67FB78FCCBFB28" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[692,824,1227,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Emesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthosa">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFD67FB78FD36FB28" box="[692,709,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFD00FB7FFCCBFB28" box="[723,824,1227,1253]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">xanthosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFCBDFB78FBD0FB28" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[878,1059,1228,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFCBDFB78FBD0FB28" box="[878,1059,1228,1254]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Sertania guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is about 9%, similar to the difference of 8% between two genera 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFDD7FB44FD0EFAC4" authority="H. Bates, 1868" authorityName="H. Bates" authorityYear="1868" box="[516,765,1263,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Lasaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFDD7FB44FDA3FAC4" box="[516,592,1264,1289]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Lasaia</emphasis>
H. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B76E926593DFDAAFB44FD0EFAC4" author="Bates, H. W." box="[633,765,1263,1290]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" pagination="373 - 436" refId="ref9000" refString="Bates, H. W. (1868) A catalogue of Erycinidae, a family of diurnal Lepidoptera. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 9, 373 - 436. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1868. tb 01224. x" type="journal article" year="1868">Bates, 1868</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFCE7FB5BFB38FAC4" authority="Grote &amp; Robinson, 1869" authorityName="Grote &amp; Robinson" authorityYear="1869" box="[820,1227,1263,1289]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Calephelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFCE7FB5BFC5FFAC4" box="[820,940,1263,1289]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Calephelis</emphasis>
Grote &amp; Robinson, 1869
</taxonomicName>
, but larger that the difference of 6.5% between two subgenera 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFD51FAA7FCEDFAE0" authorityName="Trujano-Ortega" authorityYear="2018" box="[642,798,1299,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Apodemia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Neoapodemia">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFD51FAA7FCEDFAE0" box="[642,798,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Neoapodemia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Trujano, 2018 and 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFC2FFAA7FA6AFAE0" authority="Trujano &amp; Garcia, 2018" authorityName="Trujano-Ortega &amp; Garcia-Vazquez" authorityYear="2018" box="[1020,1433,1299,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Plesioarida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFC2FFAA7FB8CFAE0" box="[1020,1151,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Plesioarida</emphasis>
Trujano &amp; García, 2018
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, similarly to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B76E926593DFE49FA83FD6AFA9C" author="Kaminski, L. A. &amp; Callaghan, C. J. &amp; Seraphim, N. &amp; Magaldi, L. M. &amp; Volkmann, L. &amp; Freitas, A. V. L." box="[410,665,1335,1362]" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" pagination="165 - 179" refId="ref9793" refString="Kaminski, L. A., Callaghan, C. J., Seraphim, N., Magaldi, L. M., Volkmann, L. &amp; Freitas, A. V. L. (2017) Sertania gen. nov., a new genus of butterflies (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae) from the South American dry diagonal. Zootaxa, 4312 (1), 165 - 179. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4312.1.8" type="journal article" year="2017">
Kaminski 
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFDDDFA8CFDCCFA9C" box="[526,575,1335,1361]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">et al</emphasis>
. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
, we do not place 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFC88FA83FC33FA9C" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[859,960,1335,1361]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Emesis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthosa">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFC88FA83FC33FA9C" box="[859,960,1335,1361]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">xanthosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D04E926593DFC30FA8CFBB1FA9F" authorityName="Callaghan &amp; Kaminski" authorityYear="2017" box="[995,1090,1336,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EA95E926593DFC30FA8CFBB1FA9F" box="[995,1090,1336,1362]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="481">Sertania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but a new genus is erected for it here.
</paragraph>
